GSG 6, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
GSG 6, LLC ("GSG") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from a wind generating facility located in Lee County, Illinois within the Commonwealth Edison Company ("ComEd") Zone of the control area administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This Rate Schedule sets forth GSG's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Supply Service, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides that PJM will pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. REVENUE REQUIREMENT: Total Revenue Requirement: GSG's Total Annual Revenue Requirement shall be calculated as follows: Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement is: $420,480.01 Monthly Revenue Requirement is: $35,040.00 (based on Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement divided by 12)

1 DM_US 183325392-8.109216.0031 4162-5046-1231.1 ASSIGNMENT, CO-TENANCY AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS ASSIGNMENT, CO-TENANCY AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is made as of December 7, 2021 (“Agreement Date”) by and among GSG 6, LLC, an Illinois limited liability company (“Shady Oaks 1”), and SHADY OAKS WIND 2, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Shady Oaks 2”). Shady Oaks 1 and Shady Oaks 2 are collectively referred to herein as the “Parties” and individually as a “Party” and are sometimes referred to collectively as the “Project Companies” or individually as a “Project Company”. The terms “Party” and “Project Company” shall include the permitted successors and permitted assignees of such Person. Certain capitalized terms used in this Agreement are given defined meanings in Appendix A attached hereto. RECITALS A. Shady Oaks 1 holds certain real property interests in the land located in Lee County, Illinois described on attached Exhibit A-1 (“Shady Oaks 1 Property”), on which it has developed a 109.5 MWAC wind energy electricity generation project and certain related interconnection facilities (“Shady Oaks 1 Project”). B. Shady Oaks 2 holds or anticipates holding certain real property interests in the land located in Lee County, Illinois described on attached Exhibit A-2 (“Shady Oaks 2 Property”), on which it intends to develop a 108.33 MWAC wind energy electricity generation project and certain related interconnection facilities (“Shady Oaks 2 Project”). The Shady Oaks 1 Project and the Shady Oaks 2 Project are each individually referred to herein as a “Project,” and collectively as the “Projects.” The Shady Oaks 1 Property and the Shady Oaks 2 Property are each individually referred to herein as a “Property,” and collectively as the “Properties.” C. Shady Oaks 1 signed that certain Interim Interconnection Service Agreement, dated as of July 16, 2021 (the “Interim ISA”) and that certain Interim Construction Service Agreement, dated as of July 20, 2021 (the “ICSA”), respectively, by and among the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (the “Transmission Service Provider” or “TSP”) and Commonwealth Edison Company (the “Transmission Owner”), for the respective Projects. Shady Oaks 1 has also signed and filed with the TSP and the Transmission Owner that certain Request for Interconnection Services Agreement (the “Application”), which Shady Oaks 1 expects will result in a final Interconnection Services Agreement (the “Final ISA”) on or about March, 2022. Collectively, the Interim ISA, the ICSA, the Application and any Final ISA, when executed, as the same may hereafter be further amended in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement, are referred to herein as the “Interconnection Agreements”. D. Shady Oaks 1, as Class A member, and Shady Oaks 2, as Class B Member, each entered into that certain Limited Liability Company Agreement for Shady Oaks Transco Interconnection, LLC (“Transco”), dated as of the date hereof (as may be amended in accordance with the terms hereof or as may be further amended, amended and restated, supplemented or otherwise modified from time to time in accordance with the terms hereof, the “Transco LLCA”).
2 DM_US 183325392-8.109216.0031 4162-5046-1231.1 Shady Oaks 1 intends to assign all of its rights, title and interest in, to and under Interconnection Agreements to Transco pursuant to an assignment agreement (the “Interconnection Assignment Agreement”) within forty-five (45) days after the execution of the Final ISA. In accordance with the Interconnection Assignment Agreement, Transco shall become a party to the Interconnection Agreements and have the rights, entitlements, obligations, responsibilities and liabilities in, to and under the Interconnection Agreements necessary for the Parties to interconnect their respective Projects. E. The Parties each individually hold or anticipate holding certain real property options, franchise, leasehold, easement, rights-of-way, encroachment rights, crossing rights, rights under non-disturbance agreements, rights under waivers, rights under consents and/or fee interests described in Exhibit B-1 (the “Land Rights Agreements”) relating to the property described in Exhibit B-2 (the “Joint Use Areas”). F. The Parties desire to provide in this Agreement for: (i) the co-ownership of certain Shared Facilities necessary or convenient to each Party’s ownership, development and operation of its respective Project; (ii) sharing of the use of such Shared Facilities for purposes of each Party’s development and operation of its respective Project; (iii) sharing use of the Joint Use Areas by each Party for its respective Project; and (iv) sharing of certain costs related to such Joint Use Areas and the construction and use and operation of such Shared Facilities; all subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. G. In the month of September 2021 (“September Outage”), certain shutdowns occurred for substation modification for the benefit of Shady Oaks 2 in which Shady Oaks 1 experienced losses. NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual promises contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged by the Parties, the Parties agree as follows: ARTICLE 1 DEFINITIONS, INTERPRETATIONS AND CONSIDERATION 1.1 Definitions. As used in this Agreement, including the Recitals, and except as required by grammatical usage and apart from proper nouns, each capitalized term has the meaning given to it in this Agreement and in the Schedule of Definitions attached as Appendix A. 1.2 Interpretation. In this Agreement, unless a clear, contrary intention appears: (a) the singular includes the plural and vice versa; (b) reference to any Person includes such Person’s successors and assigns but only if such assigns are permitted by this Agreement, and reference to a Person in a particular capacity excludes such Person in any other capacity; (c) reference to any gender includes each other gender; (d) reference to any agreement (including this Agreement), document or instrument means such agreement, document or instrument as amended or modified and in effect from time to time in accordance with the terms thereof and, if applicable, the terms of this Agreement; (e) reference to any Governmental Requirement means such Governmental Requirement as amended, modified, codified, or reenacted, in whole or in part, and in effect from time to time, including, if applicable, rules and regulations promulgated thereunder; (f) reference
3 DM_US 183325392-8.109216.0031 4162-5046-1231.1 to any Section means such Section of this Agreement, and references in any Section or definition to any clause means such clause of such Section or definition; (g) “hereunder,” “hereof,” “hereto” and words of similar import shall be deemed references to this Agreement as a whole and not to any particular Section or other provision of this Agreement; (h) “including” means including without limiting the generality of any description such term; and (i) relative to the determination of any period of time, “from” means “from and including”, “to” means “to but excluding” and “through” means “through and including”. 1.3 Consideration. Shady 2 shall pay Shady Oaks 1 the amount of Seven Hundred, Sixty Thousand Nine Hundred Ninety-Eight Dollars ($760,998) by no later than December 31, 2021 as consideration for entering into this Agreement and the agrees that for any outages after the effective date of this Agreement, Shady Oaks 2 shall pay Shady Oaks 1 for all losses suffered by Shady Oaks 1 for any such outage if the outage is for the sole benefit of Shady Oaks 2. ARTICLE 2 SHARED FACILITIES 2.1 Declaration of Intention. The Parties hereby declare that their relationship in and to the Shared Facilities is and will be that of tenants in common, and that each Project Company will have an undivided interest in proportion to their Proportionate Shares as set forth on Exhibit D in the Shared Facilities on and subject to the terms, conditions, limitations and requirements set forth in this Agreement. The arrangements and ownership structure contemplated by this Agreement are not being made with the intention or expectation of producing revenue or making or sharing in any profits from the ownership or operation of the Shared Facilities, but are instead intended as a form of legal ownership whereby the Parties can accomplish their respective objectives of independently owning and operating their respective Undivided Interests (as defined in Section 2.2(b)) in, and sharing the use of, the Shared Facilities in connection with their respective Projects and businesses and to enable the Parties to perform and discharge certain of their obligations under the Interconnection Agreements, and their respective Power Purchase Agreements. 2.2 Shared Facilities. (a) Shady Oaks 1 has constructed and is currently operating a substation on the Joint Use Areas which includes portions of the facilities for electrical transmission, interconnection, communications and other structures and facilities for shared use of the Parties (“Existing Shared Facilities”). The Parties intend to construct certain additions and upgrades to the Existing Shared Facilities for shared use by the Parties (“Shared Facilities Enhancements”). The Existing Shared Facilities as added to and upgraded by the Existing Shared Facilities are intended for shared use by the Parties and are identified on Exhibit C-1 under the heading Existing Shared Facilities and may be further altered or reconstructed in accordance with this Agreement from time to time (such facilities herein collectively, the “Shared Facilities”). The initial plans in place as of the Agreement Date for the Shared Facilities Enhancements are identified on Exhibit C-2 attached hereto (herein, the “Shared Facilities Enhancement Plans”). Shady Oaks 2 shall act as the Constructing Party for purposes of the design, procurement, installation and construction of the Shared Facilities Enhancements as identified upon the Shared Facilities Enhancement Plans, all as more particularly set forth in Section 2.6 below.
4 DM_US 183325392-8.109216.0031 4162-5046-1231.1 (b) Shady Oaks 1 shall be deemed to have GRANTED, SOLD, TRANSFERRED, ASSIGNED, and CONVEYED, and does hereby GRANT, SELL, TRANSFER, ASSIGN, AND CONVEY unto each of the Parties an undivided ownership interest in and to the Existing Shared Facilities, including rights under construction and supply contracts and contractor, supplier or manufacturer warranties related to such Existing Shared Facilities, in each case in proportion to the Proportionate Share of the respective transferee Parties, AS IS, WITH ALL FAULTS AND WITHOUT ANY REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES WHATSOEVER, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, AND SPECIFICALLY EXCLUDING ANY WARRANTY OF TITLE, MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR ANY OTHER WARRANTY ARISING UNDER STATUTORY OR COMMON LAW. As each further component of the Shared Facilities (whether the Shared Facilities Enhancements or any Additional Facilities) is constructed and installed, without limiting the reimbursement terms set forth in this Agreement, the Constructing Party shall be deemed to have GRANTED, SOLD, TRANSFERRED, ASSIGNED, and CONVEYED, and does hereby GRANT, SELL, TRANSFER, ASSIGN, AND CONVEY unto each of the Parties an undivided ownership interest in and to such further component of Shared Facilities (whether the Shared Facilities Enhancements or any Additional Facilities), including rights under construction and supply contracts and contractor, supplier or manufacturer warranties related to such Shared Facilities, in each case in proportion to the Proportionate Share of the respective transferee Parties, AS IS, WITH ALL FAULTS AND WITHOUT ANY REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES WHATSOEVER, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, AND SPECIFICALLY EXCLUDING ANY WARRANTY OF TITLE, MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR ANY OTHER WARRANTY ARISING UNDER STATUTORY OR COMMON LAW. The intent of the foregoing is that each Party shall acquire and hold an undivided tenancy in common interest in each of the Shared Facilities (whether the Initial Shared Facilities or any Additional Facilities) in proportion to its respective Proportionate Share as set forth on Exhibit D for the benefit, operation and use of its respective Project as provided herein so as to provide for the joint ownership of the Shared Facilities (along with all appurtenant rights) by the Parties subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. The foregoing undivided tenancy in common interest of each Project Company in the Shared Facilities may be referred to from time to time in this Agreement as an “Undivided Interest.” The GRANT, SALE, TRANSFER, ASSIGNMENT, and CONVEYANCE by and from Shady Oaks 1 and/or the Constructing Party unto each of the Parties shall be self-operative and shall occur automatically without further action by any Party. Without limiting the foregoing, (i) upon the request of any of the Parties, Shady Oaks 1 shall execute a bill-of-sale or other reasonably requested form of transfer acknowledging the GRANT, SALE, TRANSFER, ASSIGNMENT, and CONVEYANCE of the Existing Shared Facilities by and from Shady Oaks 1 unto each of the Project Companies; and (ii) upon completion of the Shared Facilities Enhancements, the Constructing Party shall, upon the request of any of the Parties, execute a bill-of-sale or other reasonably requested form of transfer acknowledging the GRANT, SALE, TRANSFER, ASSIGNMENT, and CONVEYANCE by and from the Constructing Party unto each of the Project Companies. Notwithstanding the foregoing or anything to the contrary herein, prior to the Shady Oaks 2 Acquisition Date, Shady Oaks 2 shall have a Proportionate Share equal to 0%.
5 DM_US 183325392-8.109216.0031 4162-5046-1231.1 (c) For the avoidance of doubt, the Parties acknowledge and agree that the Shared Facilities include any Additional Facilities, but expressly do not include equipment, materials or other property (if any) identified in Exhibit C-1 as the sole property of any Project Company or other Person. (d) Each Party intends that all rights under construction and supply contracts and contractor, supplier or manufacturer warranties related to any Shared Facilities (whether the Initial Shared Facilities or any Additional Facilities) shall benefit all Parties, and the Parties shall cooperate with each other to ensure enforceability of such contracts and any warranties available under such contracts for the benefit of the Parties, including assigning such warranties to the Parties collectively if such warranties are assignable. (e) Each Project Company may use the Shared Facilities only to transmit electrical energy from its Project to the Point of Interconnection. No Project Company will provide any interconnection or transmission services or rights to any other Person. (f) Following the execution of the Final ISA and the Interconnection Assignment Agreement, each Party hereto agree that (i) Transco shall have the right to use and operate the Shared Facilities as needed to comply with the terms of the Interconnection Agreements and to transmit the power from each Project to the Interconnection Facilities on behalf of the Parties, as members of Transco, (ii) Transco shall, if required pursuant to FERC regulations, file this Agreement pursuant to Section 4.11. As Class A Member and Class B Member under the Transco LLCA, the Parties hereto understand and agree that following the execution of the Final ISA and the Interconnection Assignment Agreement, they shall cause the Transco to accept the rights granted by subsection (i) above and authorize the Manager, on behalf of Transco and the Parties, to make any required FERC filing and coordinate the filings of the notices of concurrence as provided in subsection (ii). Manager shall not make any FERC filing unless each Party has reviewed and approved the form and content of the FERC filing. 2.3 Joint Use Areas. (a) A Party’s exercise of rights with respect to each portion of its Undivided Interest shall be subject to the Party having rights pursuant to Land Rights Agreements in favor of such Party to use the applicable Joint Use Areas on which the applicable Shared Facilities are located. Each Party shall comply with all the terms and conditions of the Land Rights Agreements to which it is a party. (b) The Land Rights Agreements as of the Agreement Date, including, if applicable, any such rights that are expected to be obtained after the Agreement Date, are described on Exhibit B-1 in the Joint Use Areas described on Exhibit B-2. (c) The Land Rights Agreements to which each Project Company is a party are the separate property of such Project Company. Each Party hereby consents to the use of the Joint Use Areas by the other Project Companies and Manager pursuant to this Agreement, including without limitation, where such Joint Use Areas affect, or otherwise touch and concern, other real property interests or estates held by such Party so long as such use is consistent with the requirements of this Agreement and the rights of the Parties hereunder. For all purposes under this
6 DM_US 183325392-8.109216.0031 4162-5046-1231.1 Agreement, the Project Companies shall share in use of the Joint Use Areas as contemplated by this Agreement and, in addition to sharing in the costs and expenses associated with the Shared Facilities as otherwise provided herein, shall share in the property taxes and rental payments and/or easement fees with respect to such Joint Use Areas in accordance with their Proportionate Shares. 2.4 Access to the Joint Use Areas and Shared Facilities. (a) By Project Companies. Subject to the conditions and additional rights described below, each Party and any Secured Party of such Party shall have access to and the right to enter onto the Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities located thereon to the extent reasonably necessary for (i) inspection of such Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities located thereon, without unduly interfering with the normal operations of the other Parties or the Manager and otherwise subject to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement, (ii) construction of the Shared Facilities in the event the Constructing Party fails to do so, in accordance with the terms hereof, (iii) Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities in the event the Manager fails to do so, in accordance with the terms hereof, (iv) for ingress and egress to and from, and for maintenance or repair of, the Shared Facilities in the event of an Emergency and the failure or unavailability of the Manager or its representatives to respond timely to such Emergency, and (v) subject to the covenants, terms and conditions of this Agreement (including, without limitation, Sections 2.5 and 4.13), for ingress and egress to and from, and for construction, maintenance or repair of, any Separately Held Property of such Project Company that are located within or to be located within the Joint Use Areas pursuant to rights granted to such Project Company in the Land Rights Agreements to which it is a party. Except in the event of an Emergency, the accessing Party shall give the other Parties and the Manager at least forty-eight (48) hours prior notice of its intent to enter upon the Joint Use Areas (said notice may be by telephone, e-mail, or any other recognized electronic means in addition to any other methods of notice authorized herein). In the event of an Emergency, prior notice is not required, but the accessing Party shall give notice of entry onto the Joint Use Areas to the other Parties and the Manager as soon as reasonably practicable thereafter). Any Project Company entering on the Joint Use Areas or accessing the Shared Facilities shall (1) follow all written safety and security procedures adopted by the Project Companies with respect to the Joint Use Areas and/or the Shared Facilities, and (2) not cause a breach or default of the terms of any binding Land Rights Agreements benefitting or burdening such Joint Use Areas where the terms thereof have been made available to the entering Project Company. (b) By Manager. The Manager shall have access to the Joint Use Areas and Shared Facilities at any time for purposes of complying with its obligations set forth in this Agreement, including (i) inspection of such Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities located thereon, without unduly interfering with the normal operations of the Project Companies and otherwise subject to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement, (ii) Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities, including repair thereof, in accordance with the terms hereof, or (iii) for ingress and egress to and from the Shared Facilities for the purposes set forth in the preceding items (i) and (ii). No notice to the Parties shall be required from Manager prior to entering the Joint Use Areas in performing Manager’s duties under this Agreement. While entering on the Joint Use Areas or accessing the Shared Facilities, the Manager shall (1) follow all written safety and security procedures adopted by the Project Companies with respect to the Joint Use Areas and/or the Shared Facilities, and (2) not cause a breach or default of the terms of any
7 DM_US 183325392-8.109216.0031 4162-5046-1231.1 binding Land Rights Agreements benefitting or burdening such Joint Use Areas where the terms thereof have been made available to the Manager. (c) By Secured Parties. A Secured Party of a Project Company shall have the right to enter onto the Joint Use Areas for the purposes described in Section 2.4(a)(i) and, in connection with or following the exercise of remedies by the Secured Party under its Security Documents, for the other purposes described in Section 2.4(a), in each case upon five (5) Business Days’ advance written notice of its entry delivered to the Manager and the Project Companies; provided that such right of entry shall be limited to normal business hours except in the case of an Emergency. Any Secured Party so entering on the Joint Use Areas or accessing the Shared Facilities shall (i) (1) follow all written safety and security procedures adopted by the Project Companies with respect to the Joint Use Areas and/or the Shared Facilities, and (2) not cause a breach or default of the terms of any binding Land Rights Agreements benefitting or burdening such Joint Use Areas where the terms thereof have been made available to the Project Company that is a debtor of such Secured Party, and (ii) not unduly interfere with the normal operations of the Project Companies and the Manager thereon. 2.5 No Interference. Each Project Company’s use of the Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities shall comply with the terms of the Land Rights Agreements and shall not interfere with the use and enjoyment by any other Project Company of its respective rights in such Joint Use Areas or Shared Facilities, subject to all the terms and provisions of this Agreement. The Parties shall cooperate in good faith to accommodate use of the Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities by each other Party. Subject to the first sentence of this Section 2.5, the use of the Joint Use Areas and the Shared Facilities by the Project Companies pursuant to and in accordance with the terms of this Agreement will not, separately or in the aggregate, be deemed to constitute an overburdening of the Joint Use Areas or the Shared Facilities or any portion of either of them. 2.6 Construction of Shared Facilities. (a) Construction of Shared Facilities. Shady Oaks 1 (as the Constructing Party) has previously constructed the Existing Shared Facilities. Shady Oaks 2 (as the Constructing Party) shall procure, install and construct the Shared Facilities Enhancements and shall, immediately upon the passage of title to such Shared Facilities Enhancements to Shady Oaks 2 (as the Constructing Party), assign and convey title to the Shared Facilities Enhancements to the Project Companies as set forth in Section 2.2(b), including rights under construction and supply contracts and contractor, supplier or manufacturer warranties related to such Shared Facilities which warranties may be enforced as provided below; provided, that if the underlying construction or supply contracts prohibit the assignment of any warranty, Shady Oaks 2 (as the Constructing Party) will cooperate with Manager and the Parties in enforcing such warranty and collecting and applying any proceeds and other benefits under such warranty to the performance of work under such warranty for the benefit of the Parties. Subject to reimbursement as set forth herein, the Constructing Party shall procure, install and construct the Additional Facilities and shall, immediately upon the passage of title to such Additional Facilities to the Constructing Party, assign and convey title to the Additional Facilities to the Project Companies as set forth in Section 2.2(b), including rights under construction and supply contracts and contractor, supplier or manufacturer warranties related to such Additional Facilities which warranties may be enforced as provided below; provided, that if the underlying construction or supply contracts prohibit the assignment of

RECITALS A. The Project Companies are parties to the Assignment, Co-Tenancy, and Shared Facilities Agreement dated as of the Agreement Date hereof (the “Shared Facilities Agreement”). Shady Oaks 1 holds certain real property interests in the land located in Lee County, Illinois described on attached Exhibit 1 (“Shady Oaks 1 Property”), on which it has developed a 109.5 MWAC wind energy electricity generation project and certain related interconnection facilities (“Shady Oaks 1 Project”). Shady Oaks 2 holds or anticipates holding certain real property interests in the land located in Lee County, Illinois described on attached Exhibit 2 (“Shady Oaks 2 Property”), on which it intends to develop a 108.325 MWAC wind energy electricity generation project and certain related interconnection facilities (“Shady Oaks 2 Project”). The Parties each individually hold or anticipate holding certain real property options, franchise, leasehold, easement, rights-of-way, encroachment rights, crossing rights, rights under non-disturbance agreements, rights under waivers, rights under consents and/or fee interests described on attached Exhibit 3 (the “Joint Use Areas”). E. The Parties intend to develop, design and construct certain Shared Facilities for the exclusive benefit, operation and use of the Projects in accordance with that the Shared Facilities Agreement and wish to enter into this Memorandum to evidence the provisions of the Shared Facilities Agreement. NOW, THEREFORE, for good and valuable consideration, the Parties hereby certify as follows: 1. Declaration of Intention. On and subject to the terms and conditions of the Shared Facilities Agreement, the Project Companies hereby declare that the relationship of the Project Companies in and to the Shared Facilities is and shall remain that of tenants-in-common holding an Undivided Interest equal to each such Project Company’s respective Proportionate Share (as such Proportionate Share is determined pursuant to the Shared Facilities Agreement). 2. Properties Benefitted and Bound. The rights and obligations of the Parties under the Shared Facilities Agreement benefit and burden each of the Properties and each Project Company’s interest in the Joint Use Areas. The covenants and obligations under the Shared Facilities Agreement are and shall be considered covenants running with the land. All sales, conveyances and other transfers of a Project Company’s Project, such Project Company’s Undivided Interests, and/or the Land Rights Agreements to which such Project Company is a Party, shall be subject to all of the terms and conditions of the Shared Facilities Agreement, whether or not expressly stated in any instrument of sale, conveyance or transfer. The covenants, terms and provisions set forth in the Shared Facilities Agreement shall inure to the benefit of the Parties hereto and any other Person having any rights in the Shared Facilities Agreement, and their respective permitted grantees, assignees, transferees, heirs, legatees, executors, administrators, successors and assigns, and all persons claiming under them. 3. Waiver of Right to Partition or Distribution. Under the Shared Facilities Agreement, each Party has acknowledged and agreed that it would be prejudicial to the interests of the Parties thereunder if any Party were to seek partition or any other type of division of the Shared Facilities or any other shared rights, assets or properties, or to file an action for such partition or division. Therefore, in consideration of such fact and for other good and valuable consideration, each of the Parties has waived and relinquished, and does hereby waive and relinquish, any and all rights that it may have to seek a partition or any other type of division of any rights or interests in the Shared Facilities or any other shared rights, assets or properties that are subject to the Shared Facilities Agreement.
